The durability and reliability of the CW380 model makes it a strong consideration as a backup gun for law enforcement.

title: For Sale:  GENUINE SINO/SOVIET SKS!!
postcontent: Rent is due and I am trying to move a couple of rifles, so the SKS safe queen has to go to a lucky new owner. Here you have a collectors rifle, a REAL Sino/Soviet SKS! For those that do not know, after World War Two, Russia sold off a lot of its SKS manufacturing equipment and parts to China and had advisors train them in production, which went on for a short amount of time before relations soured between the two giants and the Russian parts had all been used up. These rifles can be identified by Cyrillic letters prefixing the serial number, side mounted sling swivels, and the Jianshe Arsenal "26" manufacturing stamp. I will provide much more detailed photographs if you email me and prove this is not a type 56 faker, but the real deal, a rare soviet "letter gun".  The stock has some intriguing trench art, including words and symbols I cannot understand next to several "tick" marks. The barrel is in beautiful shape and quite accurate. I will throw in 80 rounds of 7.62x39 hollow point rounds to get you shooting soon. Don't pass up on this rifle SKS enthusiest, the surplus guns have dried up, and are doubling in value, so these sino soviets will soon be all but gone. Open for trades or realistic offers.
